ARTHUR M. KETSCHKE, PROSECUTOR, v. THE MAYOR AND COUNCIL OF THE BOROUGH OF WOODBRIDGE, RESPNDENTS. Submitted January term, 1929 Decided May 7, 1929.

Before Justices Black, Campbell and Case.

Por the prosecutor, Wright, Vander Burgh & McCarthy. Por the respondent, Stanton T. Lawrence. Per Curiam.

The prosecutor having filed and submitted no brief within the time limited by the rules of this court, nor at any time, the writ of certiorari is dismissed, with costs.
